Mention Murugan in either the reel copy or caption.

The song is a mesmerizing Carnatic piece drawn from the Thiruppugazh, a revered collection of Tamil devotional hymns written by the saint-poet Arunagirinathar in the 15th century.

Arunagirinathar was a Tamil Shaiva saint-poet who lived in the 14th century in Tamil Nadu, India.

Sid Sriram’s stirring rendition brings a contemporary twist to the Shivanar, resonating with profound emotional depth and divine energy.

The song encapsulates the divine grace and empowering protection of Lord 🙏🏻🌸
